1
00:00:01,687 --> 00:00:04,987
♪ ♪

2
00:00:05,397 --> 00:00:08,462
[ALARM BLARING]

3
00:00:08,467 --> 00:00:09,700
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

4
00:00:24,449 --> 00:00:26,546
[METALLIC CRASH]

5
00:00:26,551 --> 00:00:29,783
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]</i>

6
00:00:29,788 --> 00:00:33,993
<i>♪ ♪</i>

7
00:00:46,071 --> 00:00:47,638
- [GROWLING]
- [BOTH YELP]

8
00:00:56,381 --> 00:00:58,345
[ALARM BLARING]

9
00:00:58,350 --> 00:00:59,613
Gideon, what is it?

10
00:00:59,618 --> 00:01:00,947
<i>I didn't sound the alarm.</i>

11
00:01:00,952 --> 00:01:03,316
<i>It was Mr. Rory, I believe.</i>

12
00:01:03,321 --> 00:01:06,620
[GROANS] Hey.

13
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:08,121
Sorry.

14
00:01:08,126 --> 00:01:11,091
Oh, you're not used to
my nighttime makeup.

15
00:01:11,096 --> 00:01:12,592
I mean, no makeup.

16
00:01:12,597 --> 00:01:14,995
Sorry to ruin the illusion.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,164
No, you, um...

18
00:01:17,169 --> 00:01:19,432
you look just like her.

19
00:01:19,437 --> 00:01:22,869
Oh. You mean the other Zari.

20
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:25,005
Yeah.

21
00:01:25,010 --> 00:01:28,041
I could change my hair if it would help.

22
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:29,342
Help what?

23
00:01:29,347 --> 00:01:32,379
Whatever's happening down there.

24
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:34,681
<i>[MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC]</i>

25
00:01:34,686 --> 00:01:36,316
- It's not my fault.
- Mm.

26
00:01:36,321 --> 00:01:37,818
- I was sleeping.
- Yeah.

27
00:01:37,823 --> 00:01:40,053
It's natural.

28
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:42,656
Whatever you say, Steel.

29
00:01:42,661 --> 00:01:44,291
<i>[UPBEAT HIP-HOP PLAYING]</i>

30
00:01:44,296 --> 00:01:46,760
<i>Move your butts, people.
Need you on the bridge.</i>

31
00:01:46,765 --> 00:01:49,930
All right, all right. Just
gotta finish my last set.

32
00:01:49,935 --> 00:01:54,140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:56,570
Is he doing all right, Gideon?

34
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:58,304
<i>Mr. Tarazi asked me to formulate</i>

35
00:01:58,309 --> 00:02:00,707
<i>an ingestible gelatinous
cannaboid compound</i>

36
00:02:00,712 --> 00:02:01,975
<i>to help him sleep.</i>

37
00:02:01,980 --> 00:02:04,144
You make marijuana candy?

38
00:02:04,149 --> 00:02:08,154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39
00:02:08,687 --> 00:02:10,350
Sometimes I wonder if they're ever

40
00:02:10,355 --> 00:02:12,886
gonna let me back into Texas.

41
00:02:12,891 --> 00:02:14,988
[SIGHS]

42
00:02:14,993 --> 00:02:16,823
Rory, what time is it?

43
00:02:16,828 --> 00:02:19,593
<i>Technically, time doesn't
exist in the Temporal Zone.</i>

44
00:02:19,598 --> 00:02:21,895
Yes, thank you, Gideon.
I just mean it's early.

45
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,764
I got a hit on the alien
that kidnapped Sara.

46
00:02:24,769 --> 00:02:26,466
What? Why the hell didn't you wake me?

47
00:02:26,471 --> 00:02:29,002
Well, remember that sketch I drew?

48
00:02:29,007 --> 00:02:30,270
The, uh, squid face?

49
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:31,773
Oh, yeah, I thought
it was chicken wings.

50
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:34,307
Well, Gideon helped me find this photo

51
00:02:34,312 --> 00:02:36,276
buried amongst some old KGB files.

52
00:02:36,281 --> 00:02:38,044
Report about a crashed space alien.

53
00:02:38,049 --> 00:02:41,414
It was redacted until Putin
was ousted from power in 2044.

54
00:02:41,419 --> 00:02:42,816
"Redacted"? "Ousted"?

55
00:02:42,821 --> 00:02:44,484
Where are these words coming from, Rory?

56
00:02:44,489 --> 00:02:46,453
I know words.

57
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:50,557
Look, uh, thanks for cleaning me up.

58
00:02:50,562 --> 00:02:52,225
- [GRUNTS]
- Oh, thank you.

59
00:02:52,230 --> 00:02:54,861
Oh, you even smell nice.

60
00:02:54,866 --> 00:02:56,229
Gang, great news.

61
00:02:56,234 --> 00:02:58,265
Rory got a lead on the
alien that took Sara.

62
00:02:58,270 --> 00:03:00,367
Hmm. Shocking, honestly.

63
00:03:00,372 --> 00:03:01,868
Hmm.

64
00:03:01,873 --> 00:03:03,436
The pod we're looking for was picked up

65
00:03:03,441 --> 00:03:05,505
by military forces at 0600 hours.

66
00:03:05,510 --> 00:03:06,906
It's en route as we speak.

67
00:03:06,911 --> 00:03:10,076
The plan, rendezvous with it here.

68
00:03:10,081 --> 00:03:12,112
Any questions?

69
00:03:12,117 --> 00:03:14,047
<i>En route. Rendezvous.</i>

70
00:03:14,052 --> 00:03:15,916
<i>Est-ce que tu parles français, Rory?</i>

71
00:03:15,921 --> 00:03:16,921
What?

72
00:03:16,926 --> 00:03:18,556
Hey, this is great, Mick,

73
00:03:18,561 --> 00:03:20,787
but shouldn't Gideon do the coordinates?

74
00:03:20,792 --> 00:03:22,622
Already set, numb nuts.

75
00:03:22,627 --> 00:03:24,858
Wait, shouldn't we stop by John's,

76
00:03:24,863 --> 00:03:27,494
pick up him and Astra?

77
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,628
[ALL GRUNT]

78
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:32,565
<i>[ROUSING MUSIC]</i>

79
00:03:32,570 --> 00:03:33,834
Let's move.

80
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:35,603
It's a two-click hike
through thick jungle.

81
00:03:35,607 --> 00:03:37,133
Right, I love the intensity, Rory,

82
00:03:37,138 --> 00:03:38,738
but just a little heads-up
would be nice.

83
00:03:38,743 --> 00:03:41,741
Okay, hold up, I thought
this was a time machine.

84
00:03:41,746 --> 00:03:43,243
Why not bring us back an hour earlier?

85
00:03:43,247 --> 00:03:44,879
That way, y'all can
change out of your pj's.

86
00:03:44,883 --> 00:03:46,980
Oh, girl, we don't ask those questions.

87
00:03:46,985 --> 00:03:49,983
<i>[EXCITING MUSIC]</i>

88
00:03:49,988 --> 00:03:54,193
<i>♪ ♪</i>

89
00:03:54,198 --> 00:04:01,198
- Synced and corrected by<font color=#00BFFF> Firefly</font> -
- <font color=#00ffff>www.addic7ed.com</font> -

90
00:04:03,268 --> 00:04:04,998
Damn it. We forgot Behrad.

91
00:04:05,003 --> 00:04:06,934
Spooner, what did I tell you
about the Legends' buddy system?

92
00:04:06,938 --> 00:04:10,574
That hippie burnout wouldn't
want no part of this action.

93
00:04:12,911 --> 00:04:14,541
Okay, Rory, what's the plan?

94
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:15,842
Cover me.

95
00:04:15,847 --> 00:04:17,978
With what? I'm wearing slippers.

96
00:04:17,983 --> 00:04:21,114
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL BRASSY MUSIC]</i>

97
00:04:21,119 --> 00:04:25,124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

98
00:04:25,490 --> 00:04:27,891
[SHOUTING]

99
00:04:31,930 --> 00:04:33,960
Commie son of a bitch tried to shoot me!

100
00:04:33,965 --> 00:04:36,062
Think it was a bad idea
letting Rory run point?

101
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,531
Eh, we've had messier missions.

102
00:04:38,536 --> 00:04:41,067
[SCREAMS]

103
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:42,606
[HORNS HONK]

104
00:04:46,344 --> 00:04:49,442
[SHOUTING]

105
00:04:49,447 --> 00:04:50,714
Let's go.

106
00:04:56,554 --> 00:04:58,551
[SCREAMS]

107
00:04:58,556 --> 00:05:00,620
[ENGINE TURNS OVER]

108
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:02,459
I'm in! Let's go!

109
00:05:07,699 --> 00:05:09,233
[GRUNTS]

110
00:05:12,971 --> 00:05:15,402
Why is everyone shooting?

111
00:05:15,407 --> 00:05:17,174
Oh, they started it!

112
00:05:18,543 --> 00:05:19,806
<i>Time to check on the loot.</i>

113
00:05:19,811 --> 00:05:21,311
We're not bank robbers, Rory.

114
00:05:21,316 --> 00:05:23,343
Well, you wouldn't guess
it by our use of guns.

115
00:05:23,348 --> 00:05:24,579
Yeah, well, right to bear arms,

116
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:26,047
that is my Second Amendment privilege.

117
00:05:26,051 --> 00:05:27,680
The right to tell you guns suck,

118
00:05:27,685 --> 00:05:28,815
that's my First.

119
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:30,451
Okay, we're not gonna shoot the alien.

120
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:31,618
we're gonna talk to it.

121
00:05:31,623 --> 00:05:32,853
Oh, what if it doesn't wanna talk?

122
00:05:32,857 --> 00:05:33,920
Then we roast it.

123
00:05:33,925 --> 00:05:35,526
Okay, just open the crate, Rory.

124
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:38,992
Huh.

125
00:05:38,997 --> 00:05:41,127
This alien pod's different
than the last one.

126
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:43,863
That's because it's not an alien pod.

127
00:05:43,868 --> 00:05:46,032
It's a warhead from a Soviet

128
00:05:46,037 --> 00:05:48,635
SS-4 medium-range ballistic missile.

129
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,270
Uh, Rory, where are we?

130
00:05:50,275 --> 00:05:53,306
Uh, some island in the Caribbean.

131
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,675
Wouldn't happen to be
Cuba, would it, Mick?

132
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,644
Please tell me you
didn't take us to 1962.

133
00:05:57,649 --> 00:05:59,345
Why? What happened?

134
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:00,980
- Oh.
- Oh.

135
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:02,615
Rory, you just dropped us in the middle

136
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:03,783
of the Cuban Missile Crisis.

137
00:06:03,788 --> 00:06:05,518
And helped us steal a nuke.

138
00:06:05,523 --> 00:06:06,887
- So?
- So?!

139
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:09,086
This is the moment in history
when Americans and Soviets

140
00:06:09,090 --> 00:06:10,291
came to the brink of nuclear war.

141
00:06:10,295 --> 00:06:11,658
If we so much as sneeze...

142
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:12,692
okay, nobody move.

143
00:06:12,697 --> 00:06:13,793
It could be Armageddon.

144
00:06:13,798 --> 00:06:15,261
Okay, but we can still find

145
00:06:15,266 --> 00:06:17,664
the alien that'll help us find Sara.

146
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:18,969
You remembered to cloak the ship

147
00:06:18,974 --> 00:06:21,509
before we left, right?

148
00:06:24,142 --> 00:06:27,707
[PHONE RINGS]

149
00:06:27,712 --> 00:06:30,310
Yes.

150
00:06:30,315 --> 00:06:32,112
I see.

151
00:06:32,117 --> 00:06:33,250
Let him in.

152
00:06:34,619 --> 00:06:35,882
Mr. President.

153
00:06:35,887 --> 00:06:37,850
If this is about the, uh, missiles

154
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:39,452
down in Cuba, I've already been briefed.

155
00:06:39,456 --> 00:06:41,522
I'm afraid that the nukes
are the least of our problems.

156
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:42,689
These photographs were taken

157
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:45,625
on the latest U-2 pass over Cuba.

158
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:47,460
What the hell is that?

159
00:06:47,465 --> 00:06:48,796
Mr. President, it would appear

160
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,497
that the Soviets have a new bomber.

161
00:06:50,502 --> 00:06:53,137
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

162
00:06:56,024 --> 00:06:57,646
Gideon, what's the latest in D.C.?

163
00:06:57,651 --> 00:06:59,848
<i>JFK just called for an emergency meeting</i>

164
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:01,183
<i>of his top advisors.</i>

165
00:07:01,188 --> 00:07:03,320
Damn it, that's what I get
for letting Rory run point

166
00:07:03,325 --> 00:07:04,326
in the middle of the Cold War.

167
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:05,660
- It's all good.
- Is it?

168
00:07:05,665 --> 00:07:08,106
JFK delivered a masterclass in diplomacy

169
00:07:08,111 --> 00:07:09,741
during the Cuban Missile Crisis.

170
00:07:09,746 --> 00:07:10,809
How do I know this?

171
00:07:10,814 --> 00:07:12,744
Because I wrote my
doctoral thesis on it.

172
00:07:12,749 --> 00:07:14,149
You wanna go to Washington.

173
00:07:14,154 --> 00:07:15,552
[AS JFK] With your permission, Captain,

174
00:07:15,556 --> 00:07:16,557
I would love to throw the ball...

175
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,191
No. No. Lose the accent.

176
00:07:18,196 --> 00:07:19,772
- Way to wear that suit, though.
- Thank you.

177
00:07:19,776 --> 00:07:22,253
Aw. Thanks, girl.

178
00:07:22,258 --> 00:07:23,888
What happened to your totem?

179
00:07:23,893 --> 00:07:25,523
Oh, old one clashed.

180
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:27,358
I take it you wanna go
to Washington too.

181
00:07:27,363 --> 00:07:28,926
Yes, I spent a lot of time on this.

182
00:07:28,931 --> 00:07:31,029
Ah, morning, team. What'd I miss?

183
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:32,264
Nate and Zari are gonna make sure

184
00:07:32,268 --> 00:07:34,030
that JFK doesn't start World War III.

185
00:07:34,035 --> 00:07:35,133
The rest of us are chasing down

186
00:07:35,137 --> 00:07:36,587
a displaced space alien in Cuba.

187
00:07:36,592 --> 00:07:38,492
- No big deal.
- Cool. I'll just be...

188
00:07:38,497 --> 00:07:40,227
Ah, you will just be with me. Let's go.

189
00:07:40,232 --> 00:07:42,262
- Come on.
- [GROANING]

190
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:45,299
[WHISPERING] We're gonna
go see the Kennedys!

191
00:07:45,304 --> 00:07:48,002
Good news, Captain. We found the pod.

192
00:07:48,007 --> 00:07:50,214
It's currently on its way
to Fidel Castro's

193
00:07:50,219 --> 00:07:51,482
not-so-secret bunker.

194
00:07:51,487 --> 00:07:53,618
Wow, you found the alien
using your powers?

195
00:07:53,623 --> 00:07:55,620
Nah. CB radio.

196
00:07:55,625 --> 00:07:57,855
<i>[SOLDIER SPEAKING SPANISH]</i>

197
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:58,990
<i>De nada, Capitan.</i>

198
00:07:58,995 --> 00:08:01,059
Mm-hmm. Right.

199
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:04,695
Easiest way in is here.
I'm guessing four guards.

200
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,632
- We just blow the place to smi...
- Okay, I'll take it from here.

201
00:08:07,637 --> 00:08:09,968
They're not gonna let you just
walk through the front door.

202
00:08:09,972 --> 00:08:11,836
That's exactly what they're gonna do.

203
00:08:11,841 --> 00:08:13,604
Let's go. Behrad, come with me.

204
00:08:13,609 --> 00:08:16,007
Why do you keep grabbing
me? Look, Captain.

205
00:08:16,012 --> 00:08:18,076
Authoritarian leaders, secret bunkers,

206
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:20,011
nuclear missiles, I'm just not

207
00:08:20,016 --> 00:08:21,416
feeling the energy of this mission.

208
00:08:21,421 --> 00:08:23,082
Too bad, because I need
your energy, okay?

209
00:08:23,087 --> 00:08:24,817
Can't afford any hotheads
starting a nuclear war.

210
00:08:24,821 --> 00:08:26,217
Hey, I'm just trying to help you

211
00:08:26,222 --> 00:08:27,652
find your girlfriend.

212
00:08:27,657 --> 00:08:29,451
You know what you can help
me do is get the missile

213
00:08:29,455 --> 00:08:30,856
back to the people
that we stole it from.

214
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:32,220
Wait, the Russians?

215
00:08:32,225 --> 00:08:33,825
That defeats the purpose of stealing.

216
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:35,460
Our job is to protect history.

217
00:08:35,465 --> 00:08:37,099
Remember that next time.

218
00:08:39,569 --> 00:08:42,967
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING]

219
00:08:42,972 --> 00:08:45,436
Oye, oye. Where do you
think you're going?

220
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:47,238
Sorry, brother, we just
got turned around.

221
00:08:47,243 --> 00:08:49,440
Is there another entrance
we can maybe try?

222
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:52,310
- Who is your companion?
- Oh, uh, she's...

223
00:08:52,315 --> 00:08:54,679
[IN RUSSIAN ACCENT] I am
Dr. Yevgania Shostenko.

224
00:08:54,684 --> 00:08:56,247
At ease, comrade.

225
00:08:56,252 --> 00:08:57,715
Who are you here to see?

226
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:00,451
Um, that's classified?

227
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:02,253
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]</i>

228
00:09:02,258 --> 00:09:03,921
It's cool. We can come back later.

229
00:09:03,926 --> 00:09:06,657
Oh, no, please. We enter now. It's...

230
00:09:06,662 --> 00:09:08,860
What kind of doctor are you?

231
00:09:08,865 --> 00:09:11,196
Em...

232
00:09:11,201 --> 00:09:13,331
[CLEARS THROAT]

233
00:09:13,336 --> 00:09:17,541
The kind who specializes in
extraterrestrial creatures.

234
00:09:20,042 --> 00:09:22,140
Why didn't you say so?

235
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:23,912
Follow me.

236
00:09:29,719 --> 00:09:32,583
We're supposed to give the
nuke to the Russkies, right?

237
00:09:32,588 --> 00:09:35,119
Well, those ain't Russkies.

238
00:09:35,124 --> 00:09:37,488
Uh, permission to shoot our way

239
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,524
out of a sticky situation, Captain.

240
00:09:39,529 --> 00:09:41,125
No, absolutely not.

241
00:09:41,130 --> 00:09:42,961
The last thing we need is
an international incident.

242
00:09:42,965 --> 00:09:44,896
- Do you copy?
<i>- Uh-huh.</i>

243
00:09:44,901 --> 00:09:46,531
Was that a "yes" grunt or a "no"?

244
00:09:46,536 --> 00:09:47,699
<i>[GRUNTS]</i>

245
00:09:47,704 --> 00:09:49,467
That's what I thought.

246
00:09:49,472 --> 00:09:51,836
Just let me do the talking, okay?

247
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:56,046
<i>♪ ♪</i>

248
00:10:01,684 --> 00:10:04,081
Sorry, we, uh, found
this rig in the jungle.

249
00:10:04,085 --> 00:10:06,051
We're just trying to get it
back to our Soviet comrades.

250
00:10:06,055 --> 00:10:07,652
It is a stolen missile!

251
00:10:07,657 --> 00:10:09,888
Yeah, we'd hate for a nuke
to fall into the wrong hands.

252
00:10:09,892 --> 00:10:12,190
Which is why I must take it
to El Comandante immediately.

253
00:10:12,195 --> 00:10:14,892
- El who?
- Fidel freakin' Castro.

254
00:10:14,897 --> 00:10:17,762
Sir, wouldn't the Soviets prefer
that we return it to them?

255
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:18,863
You don't understand.

256
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:21,066
The North Americans have
